wikipedia_page.main: James Liddell (born 1897) was a Scottish footballer who played for Albion Rovers, Dumbarton and Clyde.He joined Liverpool in 1920 but failed to make any first team appearances in his year at Anfield, moving on to Bristol Rovers in 1921. In two and a half years in Bristol he made thirty league appearances, scoring either 4 or 5 goals. In January 1924 he moved to First Division side Preston North End, but as with his time in Liverpool, he didn't make any first team appearances for them.
